          <h2
            class="text-2xl font-light tracking-wide mb-8 text-secondary-300 uppercase">
            Biographical Information
          </h2>
          <div class="prose-lg text-secondary-500 leading-relaxed space-y-6">
            <p>
              Tobias <em class="font-light italic text-secondary-400"
                >"Logic Moon"</em
              > Lorsbach comes from Mainz, Germany. He began his musical career as
              a DJ and was active in the minimal techno scene in the early 2000s.
              At the same time, he played guitar in a death metal band until he increasingly
              turned to ambient music.
            </p>
            <p>
              During a <strong class="font-medium text-secondary-400"
                >field recording trip</strong
              >, the idea arose to combine ambient drone elements with his
              recordings – this resulted in his debut album <em
                class="italic text-secondary-400">Herbst11</em
              > as Logic Moon in 2013. His compositions often begin with a guitar
              sketch, followed by synthesizers and other layers.
            </p>
            <p>
              This <strong class="font-medium text-secondary-400"
                >cross-genre background</strong
              > (techno, metal, ambient) shapes his stylistic approach: The press
              describes that Tobias as Logic Moon makes "guitar-oriented ambient
              and drone music" and his music is often perceived as "lively" and as
              a balance between classical accessibility and experimental discovery.
            </p>
